===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} ''pteridos'' (fern) + [[-phyte]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any [[simple]] [[vascular plant]] that produces [[spore]]s, but not [[seed]]s, and has the [[diploid]] stage of its [[life cycle]] as the [[dominant]] form.
#: ''Ferns, lycopods, and scouring rushes are all '''pteridophytes'''.''

